{
  "texts": [
    "Here, M is the number of test samples originally classified correctly and N is the number of perturbations sampled for each input.",
    "Later, Robey et al. (2022) proposed quantile accuracy ProbAcc(ρ) to evaluate PR for individual inputs using the same perturbation strategy (uniform sampling around each input).",
    "Unlike PR D (γ), which estimates the mean PR over all correctly classified clean test samples, this metric focuses on a given robustness tolerance threshold ρ.",
    "Specifically, ProbAcc(ρ) measures the proportion of inputs whose PR(x, γ) exceeds the threshold 1 -ρ, formally defined as follows:",
    "In PRBench, we assess the PR of different training methods using both PR D (γ) and ProbAcc(ρ)."
  ]
}